BFN 

  [Text] According to a poll conducted by Doctor of 
Sociological Sciences Kotlyarow, director of the Center for 
Political and Socioeconomic Analysis, 75 percent of Belarusian 
citizens consider price hikes the most important problem facing 
Belarus. More than half of society -- 54.3 percent -- consider 
the crime rate the most important problem. As RID has learned, 
corruption within state authorities comes in third. It worries 
38.8 percent of Belarusian citizens. 

